Authentication method of web services
1)Authentication->who you are
2)Authorize->what you can do

HTTP Basic Authentication->username:password encoded in base 64 and placed in HTTP header
Using SSL channels and TLS is must (HTTPS)
simple but rarely used

2)Bearer Authentication(token authentication)-> give access to the bearer of the token
the token allowing access to certain resource or URL is a cryptic string generated by server
in response to login request1)
Client must send this token in authorization header when